<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id6b50a0a0-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e" identifier="/us/usc/t33/s634"><num value="634">§ 634.</num><heading> Assistance relating to water supply</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary may provide assistance to municipalities the water supply of which is adversely affected by construction carried out by the Corps of Engineers.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id6b50a0a1-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e">(<ref href="/us/pl/115/270/tI/s1114">Pub. L. 115–270, title I, § 1114</ref>, <date date="2018-10-23">Oct. 23, 2018</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/132/3776">132 Stat. 3776</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id6b50a0a2-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="id6b50a0a3-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I87" topic="miscellaneous" id="id6b50a0a4-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e">
<heading class="centered smallCaps">“Secretary” Defined</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Secretary means the Secretary of the Army, see <ref href="/us/pl/115/270/s102">section 102 of Pub. L. 115–270</ref>, set out as a note under <ref href="/us/usc/t33/s2201">section 2201 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
